    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      Main used for selects the option to run the program.

      Implementor runs in 2 ways:

      • with 2 args: run with this arguments
      • with 3 args: run with second and third argument
      If args are incorrect: Error is displayed on the console
      Parameters:
      args - command line arguments to run the program

    • implementJar

      public void implementJar(Class<?> token, Path jarFile) throws ImplerException
      Creates .jar file with compiled implementing interface. Created class with same name of classtoken + IMPL
      Specified by:
      implementJar in interface JarImpler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      jarFile - target .jar file.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - if can't generate implementation file because one or more of these reasons:
      • 1) token == null
      • 2) Can't recognise and create Path of jarFile
      • 3) {}compile(Class, Path)} can't compile file
      • 4) IOException with writing
      • 5) {implement(Class, Path)} can't implement interface

    • getNameWithPackage

    • implement

      public void implement(Class<?> token, Path root) throws ImplerException
      Creates java file - interface that implements token interface. Generated class will be named - token name of class + Impl. It will be located in root directory. All methods will return null/0/false.
      Specified by:
      implement in interface Impler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      root - root directory where will be located implementing java file.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - if will be one or more of these reasons:
      • 1) token is not interface or private
      • 2) root is incorrect path
      • 3) IOException with writing
      • 4) IOException can't create directory root
